  "signal_description": "The query retrieves various metrics related to invoice processing. It selects the following columns from the 'defaultview-225' table: 'Inv. Company Code Text', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Number', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Name', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Country', 'Inv. Converted USD Amount', 'case_id', 'Payment Block Rate', 'Inv. Accounting Document Number', 'Last Inv. Item Due Date', 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date', 'Inv. Posting Document Date', 'Event Created By User Type', 'event_name', 'Total Cycle Time', and 'Payment Block Duration'. The query then calculates the following metrics: 'Invoice Amount in $' (sum of 'Inv. Converted USD Amount'), 'No. of Invoices' (count of 'case_id'), 'Ø Payment Block Rate in %' (average of 'Payment Block Rate'), 'Ø Days Posting to Net Due Date' (average of the difference between 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' and 'Inv. Posting Document Date'), 'Automatic Invoice Posting in %' (percentage of invoices where 'Event Created By User Type' is 'System' and 'event_name' is 'Post Invoice'), 'Rework Rate in %' (percentage of invoices with more than one occurrence of an event other than 'Create Goods Receipt'), 'Change Rate in %' (percentage of invoices with an event name containing the word 'change'), and 'Late Payment Rate in %' (percentage of invoices where 'Last Inv. Item Due Date' is earlier than 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' and 'Last Inv. Item Clearing Date' is not null). The query groups the results by 'Inv. Company Code Text', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Number', 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Name', and 'Last Inv. Item Vendor Country', and sorts the results by 'Vendor Name' in descending order."
}
